narratives.question_text:
What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Basic music theory skills, reading music, introduced to basic Western musical concepts.
I know have a much greater sense of music theory, sight reading, etc. which will help in composition  and performance.
My musical skills have improved. I learned a lot of concepts and am able to make my own composition now.

narratives.question_text:
What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: The small class size helped me engage with the material more closely. However for such a hands on class its kind of long which is draining
The biggest strength is the small class size which allowed me to have individual time with my professor.

narratives.question_text: Among the practices in this course geared toward learning during the COVID-19 pandemic, which succeeded and which could be improved? Please comment on course practices that allowed for virtual engagement. (Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: Screen share was implanted really well especially for notation practice

Music is a more difficult subject to learn online. Professor Dubios did an excellent job with what she was given. If needed she would join the class on two different devices to be able to play music off of one.

narratives.question_text:
Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
(Your anonymous response to this question may be viewed by Yale College students, faculty, and advisers to aid in course selection and evaluating teaching.)
comments: If they want to do something for fun but something still challenging, they should!
Yes, its important to have some musical literacy especially as a performer!
Yes, it is interesting seeing how different combinations of notes leave a certain impression.
